                        "value": "Historical/Biographical Note"
                    }
                ],
                "p": [
                    {
                        "value": "Bernhard J. Stern (1894-1956) was a social scientist and political radical who came under persecution from Congressional investigative committees during the McCarthy period. The materials in the collection were assembled by Samuel W. Bloom, a sociology professor who wrote an article on Stern, \"The Intellectual in a Time of Crisis,\" for Volume 26 of the \u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-italic\"\u003eJournal of the History of the Behavioral Sciences\u003c/span\u003e."
                    }
                ]
            }
